  "prompt": "Can I catch a strep throat infection from a hug from my girlfriend?",
  "response": "Strep throat is primarily spread through respiratory droplets when an infected person coughs or sneezes. It can also be spread by direct contact with saliva. While it is less likely to catch strep throat from just a hug, if your girlfriend has strep throat and there is close contact involving sneezing, coughing, or saliva, there is a higher chance of transmission. It is always good to practice good hygiene, such as washing hands frequently and avoiding close contact if someone is sick.",
